Dataset 1 – OBD-II Vehicle Sensor Dataset
Purpose

Provides real-time vehicle sensor readings that simulate live data from a connected vehicle through the OBD-II interface.

Dataset Statistics
Original Rows: 60,439
Final Rows after cleaning: 34,397
Final Features: 18
Major Preprocessing Decisions
Removed metadata columns (Timestamp, Vehicle ID, Manufacturer, etc.).
Converted percentage values and comma-separated decimals to numeric format.
Removed rows with excessive missing values.
Filled remaining missing values using median imputation.
Encoded categorical features:
AUTOMATIC → 0/1
FUEL_TYPE → Numeric
Engineered Features
Engine Stress Index
Thermal Stress
Driving Score
Air Flow Index
Engine Efficiency
Indian Road Severity Index (IRSI)
Important Observations
1. Dataset is not labeled

There is no target column indicating vehicle failure.

Implication: This dataset is suitable for:

Live monitoring
Feature extraction
Health scoring
Dashboard visualization

It cannot be directly used to train a failure prediction model.

2. Large amount of missing values

Some sensor fields contained over 40% missing values.

Rows with excessive missing values were removed before imputation.

3. Engine Stress features show strong correlation

Engine Stress Index is highly correlated with:

Engine Load
Engine RPM

This is expected because it is a derived feature.

Member 1 may later remove correlated variables if required.

4. Dataset resembles live OBD-II sensor stream

This dataset is ideal for:

Raspberry Pi simulation
Edge AI inference
Real-time dashboard
Explainable AI


Dataset 2 – AI4I Predictive Maintenance Dataset
Purpose

Used for predictive maintenance model training.

Dataset Statistics
Rows: 10,000
Features: 15
Target:
Machine Failure
Engineered Features
Temperature Difference
Mechanical Stress
Wear Rate
Important Observations
1. Severe Class Imbalance ⭐

Machine Failure

Normal Operation : 9661

Failure : 339

Only

3.39%

of observations represent failures.

Implication

Without imbalance handling,

the model will mostly predict

Normal Operation

and still achieve very high accuracy.

Accuracy alone will therefore be misleading.

Recommendation

During model training, consider

SMOTE
ADASYN
Class Weighting
Balanced Random Forest
XGBoost with scale_pos_weight

Evaluation metrics should include

Precision
Recall
F1 Score
ROC-AUC

instead of only Accuracy.

2. Dataset is already labeled

Unlike Dataset 1,

this dataset contains

Machine Failure

making it suitable for supervised learning.

3. Failure Categories

Machine Failure is accompanied by

Tool Wear Failure
Heat Dissipation Failure
Power Failure
Overstrain Failure
Random Failure

These can later support Explainable AI.

Example:

Failure predicted because Heat Dissipation Failure probability is high.

4. Synthetic Dataset

AI4I is an industrial benchmark dataset.

Real-world deployment should combine it with live OBD-II sensor data.

Dataset 3 – Driving Behaviour Dataset
Purpose

Captures road conditions and driving behaviour.

Dataset Statistics

Original Rows

7392

Duplicates

0

Engineered Features
Vehicle Stress Index
Road Impact Score
Driving Aggressiveness
Fuel Efficiency Score
Important Observations
1. Road labels are already available ⭐

Dataset already provides

Road Surface
Traffic Condition
Driving Style

These eliminate the need to infer these conditions manually.

2. Highly suitable for Indian Road Analysis

Road surface variations

combined with

vertical acceleration

can simulate

potholes
rough roads
uneven roads

which aligns with the project objective.

3. No failure labels

Like Dataset 1,

this dataset has

no target variable.

It should not be used for failure prediction.

Instead,

it provides context that improves prediction quality.

4. Useful for Explainable AI

Example explanation

High engine stress occurred while driving aggressively on uneven roads under heavy traffic.

instead of

Failure probability = 0.83

This significantly improves explainability.

5. Good feature diversity

Dataset contains

Engine behaviour
Vehicle dynamics
Driver behaviour
Road condition

making it useful for

Road-aware Edge AI.

Final Recommendation for Member 1
Dataset	Use
OBD-II	Live Edge AI inference
AI4I	Train predictive maintenance model
Driving Behaviour	Road-condition context + driver behaviour analysis
Integration Strategy
Live OBD-II Data
        │
        ▼
Feature Engineering
        │
        ▼
Road Context
(from Dataset 3)
        │
        ▼
Predictive Model
(trained on Dataset 2)
        │
        ▼
Explainable AI
        │
        ▼
Driver Alert